HEADWORD: Ideography
<hw>I`de*og"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
representation of ideas independently of sounds, or in an ideographic
manner, as sometimes is done in shorthand writing, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

